wikipedia_page.main: Richard Mocket (also Moket or Moquet) (1577–1618) was an English churchman and academic, Warden of All Souls' College, Oxford from 1614.

response: * God and the King; or a Dialogue wherein is treated of Allegiance due to ... K. James within his Dominions, which (by removing all Controversies and Causes of Dissentions and Suspitions) bindeth Subjects by an inviolable band of Love and Duty to their Soveraigne, translated from the Latin, Cologne, 1620.Extracts from God and the King . This was a parody, Latin original (1619) Deus et rex, of the work of the same title (1615) usually attributed to Richard Mocket.
